@political_system
new-page: true

= Polish Political System

Poland is a parliamentary republic. The Sejm is elected by proportional representation in multi-member districts, with thresholds that decide whether votes convert into seats at all.

In January 2014, the player is outside government. The PO-PSL coalition governs, Donald Tusk is prime minister, and Bronislaw Komorowski is president.

- @library: Back to library.

@electoral_thresholds
new-page: true

= Electoral Thresholds

A party list must clear 5 percent nationally to enter the Sejm. A coalition list must clear 8 percent.

This is the central 2015 design problem. Running alone lowers the threshold but narrows the left's ceiling. Running as a coalition broadens the list but creates a cliff edge.

